--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Renamer
(c) 2008 Petr Nohejl

Renamer je jednoduchý nástroj pro dávkové přejmenování souborů a adresářů.
Umožňuje vkládání, nahrazení a mazání znaků v názvu souboru či adresáře.
Podporuje regulární výrazy, filtrování souborů, změnu velikosti písmen, práci s
koncovkami a zobrazuje náhled cílového názvu.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Instalace:

Renamer je aplikace využívající grafické uživatelské rozhraní TKinter a je
napsána v jazyce Python 2.6. Pro její spuštění je třeba mít nainstalován
interpret jazyka Python, který lze stáhnout na adrese: www.python.org. Knihovna
TKinter je součástí instalačního balíčku Python.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Ovládání: 

CHOOSE THE WORK DIRECTORY:
Press Open button and choose dir or set the path in the text array.

SELECT THE TYPE OF OBJECTS:
select the type of objects, which you want to rename, you can choose files,
directories or both.

USE THE FILTER:
You can use the filter, which uses Unix style pattern expansion, for show only
some files or dirs from work dir, set the filter and press enter or Refresh
button, you should see the list of objects, which you chose, it shows current
name, new name, type, size, examples: * show all; *.jpg show files with
extension .jpg; *.?? show files with 2-chars extension; [a-cz]* show files with
first letter a,b,c,z.

USE THE INSERT FUNCTION:
This function insert a string into the filename, check the Insert checkbox and
enter the string, set the position, where the string will be placed, check the
Reverse checkbox to count the position reversly, check the Extension checkbox if
you want to work also with the file extension.

USE THE REPLACE FUNCTION:
This function replace some string with another string, check the Replace
checkbox and enter the strings, check the Count checkbox and enter the count
number (integer) if you want to replace the string only n-times, check the
Interval checkbox and enter the interval numbers (integers) if you want to
replace the string only on specific interval, you can also use negative indexes
in the interval, first index must be smaller and both indexes must be only
positive or only negative, examples: 0 1 means first letter; 3 8 means
4. - 8. letters, -1 0 means last letter, -3 0 means last three letters, check
the Regular expression checkbox if you want to work with regular expression
(uses in first text array), check the Extension checkbox if you want to work
also with the file extension.

USE THE CASE SENSITIVITY FUNCTION:
This function convert string to lower or upper case letters or swap the case
letters, check the Case sensitivity checkbox and choose one of the options,
check the Interval checkbox and enter the interval numbers (integers) if you
want to convert the string only on specific interval, you can also use negative
indexes in the interval, first index must be smaller and both indexes must be
only positive or only negative, check the Extension checkbox if you want to work
also with the file extension.

PREVIEW & RENAME:
Before renaming, you must press Preview button to refresh the new filenames,
press Preview button, select the objects from the list, which you want to
rename, press the Rename button and your files or dirs will be renamed, press
Select all button if you want to select all objects in the list, press Deselect
all button if you want to deselect all objects in the list, press Clear button
if you want to clear all text arrays in Insert, Replace and Case sensitivity
functions.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
